The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 12-year-old kidnapped

 Samastipur, Feb. 6 (PTI): The kidnap saga continued in Bihar after a gang of unidentified gunmen abducted a Class VII student of Samastipur district late last night.

 Heavily-armed criminals raided the house of a retired school principal, Ramanarayan Prasad Singh and abducted his 12-year-old nephew Harsh Ranjan at gunpoint, police said today.

 The gunmen looted cash and valuables worth over Rs 1 lakh during the three-hour operation and mercilessly beat up Singh?s family members when they resisted, the police added.

 Harsh Ranjan is son of Vishnudeo Prasad, brother of the retired principal.

 Samastipur superintendent of police Meghnath Ram said he has deputed an officer of the rank of DSP to probe into the case.

 Singh has lodged and FIR in this connection and police are conducting raids at different places to rescue the boy and track down the kidnappers. 




